child who was to see, inaugurate, and typify the new age, was a real infant, born or expected in 40 13.C., and probably a son

of Pollio himself: (3) that the poet drew his ideas and imagery from Sibylline verses now lost, from Hesiod, from Orphic poets‚ possibly even from Hebrew propheti, and to some extent from his Roman predecessors.
